https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/xGWj1KVwjeGUc0bGaOoBGVeoMsa.jpg The film is about the relations between the inhabitants of Russia and the Caucasus, and about their influence on each other. Young Georgian Georgi Iobadze tells the audience the story of the Vainakhs (a group of peoples of the North Caucasus and Georgia) in the period from 1813 to 1913. Big Snakes of Ulli-Kale
